#Seperated categorical and numerical variables for descriptive analysis

analyze_categorical <- function(variable) {
freq <- table(variable)
freq_df <- as.data.frame(freq)
colnames(freq_df) <- c("Category", "Count")
freq_df <- freq_df[order(freq_df$Count, decreasing = TRUE), ]
print(freq_df)
}
#Extract categorical variables
categorical_diabetes <- diabetes[, sapply(diabetes, is.character) ] 
#Extract numerical variables
numerical_diabetes <- diabetes[, sapply(diabetes, is.numeric) ]

#Below is the creation of a visualization of the summary statistics, the each bar represents a summary statistic # 1st:Min , 2nd:1st quart , 3rd:Median , 4th:Mean, 5th:3rd quart , 6th:Max

# Descriptive analysis of numeric variables
Age_summary <- summary(diabetes$age)
Hypertension_summary <- summary(diabetes$hypertension)
Heart_disease_summary <- summary(diabetes$heart_disease)
BMI_summary <- summary(diabetes$bmi)
HbA1c_summary <- summary(diabetes$HbA1c_level)
Blood_glucose_level_summary <- summary(diabetes$blood_glucose_level)
Diabetes_summary <- summary(diabetes$diabetes)
# Convert summary statistics into numeric vectors
Age_vals <- as.numeric(Age_summary)
Hypertension_vals <- as.numeric(Hypertension_summary)
Heart_disease_vals <- as.numeric(Heart_disease_summary)
BMI_vals <- as.numeric(BMI_summary)
HbA1c_vals <- as.numeric(HbA1c_summary)
Blood_glucose_vals <- as.numeric(Blood_glucose_level_summary)
Diabetes_vals <- as.numeric(Diabetes_summary)
# Set the layout for the plot grid
par(mfrow = c(3, 2))
# Create individual bar plots for each numeric variable
barplot(Age_vals, main = "Ages of Individuals")
barplot(Hypertension_vals, main = "Individuals Experiencing Hypertension")
barplot(Heart_disease_vals, main = "Individuals with Heart Disease")
barplot(BMI_vals, main = "BMI Values")
barplot(HbA1c_vals, main = "HbA1c Level")
barplot(Blood_glucose_vals, main = "Blood Glucose Values")

barplot(Diabetes_vals, main = "Individuals with Diabetes")

#Boxplots for the numeric variables

numeric_vars <- c("age", "hypertension", "heart_disease", "bmi", "HbA1c_level", "blood_glucose_level", "diabetes")
# Set the layout for the plot grid
par(mfrow = c(2, 4))
# Create boxplots for each numerical variable
for (var in numeric_vars) {
# Plot the boxplot
boxplot(diabetes[[var]], main = var)
}

#Removing outliers from the data #For BMI I removed the values over fifty as they are extremely abnormal values that indicate severe obesity which would effect the model, for HbA1c I chose to remove above an 8.2 because above 8 is associated with having poorly controlled diabetes (I specifically chose 8.2 because If I choose 8 exact it would have cut off a large number of individuals who fit the criteria), for blood glucose I choose above two hundred as any higher is associated directly to being linked with diabetes.

eliminatedBMI <- numerical_diabetes$bmi > 50
cleandiabetes <- subset(numerical_diabetes, !eliminatedBMI)

eliminatedHbA1c <- cleandiabetes$HbA1c_level > 8.2
cleandiabetes <- subset(cleandiabetes, !eliminatedHbA1c)

eliminatedBloodglucose <- cleandiabetes$blood_glucose_level > 201
cleandiabetes <- subset(cleandiabetes, !eliminatedBloodglucose)

#nonoutlier data boxplots

# Set the layout for the plot grid
par(mfrow = c(2, 4))
# Create boxplots for each numerical variable
for (var in numeric_vars) {
# Plot the boxplot
boxplot(cleandiabetes[[var]], main = var)
}

#further descriptive analysis, histograms for all the numeric variables

par(mfrow = c(2, 3)) # Set the layout for the plot grid
for (var in numeric_vars) {
hist(diabetes[[var]], main = var, xlab = var)
}

#Switching to the categorical variables, showing the counts of each category of the two variables

# Now Analyzing Categorical variables
for (col in names(categorical_diabetes)) {
cat("\n")
cat("Variable:", col, "\n")
analyze_categorical(diabetes[[col]])
}

eliminatedHbA1c2 <- diabetes2$HbA1c_level > 8.2

#Continued Feature Selection through stepwise regression which utilizes both foward and backward as methods

full_model <- lm(scaledDiabetes$diabetes ~ ., data = scaledDiabetes)
both_step_model <- step(full_model, direction = "both")
